# Pull Request Templates and Team Standards

## Standard PR Template

```markdown
### Type of Change
- [ ] Bug fix (non-breaking)
- [ ] New feature (non-breaking)
- [ ] Breaking change
- [ ] Documentation | Performance | Refactoring | Test | CI/CD

### Description
Brief description of changes.

### Related Issues
Closes #123 | Fixes #456 | Related to #789

### Testing
- [ ] Unit | Integration | E2E tests pass
- [ ] Manual testing completed

### Checklist
- [ ] Code follows style guidelines | Self-review done
- [ ] No console.log/TODO in production code
- [ ] Error handling | Security | Performance considered
```

## Feature PR Template

```markdown
### Feature Description
Brief description of the feature.

### Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Criterion 1
- [ ] Criterion 2

### Technical Summary
Architecture, DB/API/Frontend changes, security considerations.

### Breaking Changes
- [ ] None | Document below

### Rollback Plan
How to rollback if issues arise.
```

## Bug Fix PR Template

```markdown
### Bug Description
What the bug was and its impact.

### Root Cause
What caused it and why.

### Fix
How the bug was fixed.

### Verification Steps
1. Step 1
2. Step 2

### Regression Testing
- [ ] Existing functionality intact
- [ ] No new bugs | Performance | Security unchanged
```

## Hotfix PR Template

```markdown
### Issue
Critical issue requiring immediate fix.

### Severity
Critical | High | Medium | Low — affected users, business impact.

### Fix
Quick description of the fix.

### Deployment Plan
- [ ] Ready for immediate deployment
- [ ] Rollback plan prepared | Monitoring configured

### Post-Deployment
- [ ] Monitor 24h | Verify in production | Schedule follow-up
```

## Commit Conventions

**Format:** `<type>[optional scope]: <description>`

| Type | Use |
|------|-----|
| feat | New feature |
| fix | Bug fix |
| docs | Documentation only |
| style | Formatting, no logic change |
| refactor | Code change, no bug fix or feature |
| perf | Performance improvement |
| test | Add or fix tests |
| chore | Build, tooling, deps |
| ci | CI config |
| build | Build system |
| revert | Revert previous commit |

**Good:** `feat(auth): add OAuth2 support` | `fix(api): handle null response` | `docs(readme): update install steps`

**Bad:** `fix bug` | `update code` | `add stuff` | `wip` | `fixes`

## Branch Naming

**Format:** `<type>/<issue>-<description>`

Examples: `feature/123-oauth2-integration` | `bugfix/456-login-error` | `hotfix/789-security-patch` | `refactor/101-extract-auth`

## Code Review Standards

### Review Checklist

| Check | |
|-------|---|
| Code follows project conventions | |
| No obvious bugs; error handling appropriate | |
| Security and performance considered | |
| Tests comprehensive; documentation updated | |
| No debugging code left behind | |

### Response Times

| Change Size | Target |
|------------|--------|
| Small (< 50 lines) | 4 hours |
| Medium (50–200 lines) | 8 hours |
| Large (> 200 lines) | 24 hours |
| Critical/Hotfix | 2 hours |

### Approval Requirements

| Branch Type | Approvals |
|-------------|-----------|
| Feature | Minimum 2 |
| Bug fix | Minimum 1 |
| All | CI passes, no conflicts, docs updated |

## Quality Gates

Checklist for CI/CD (implement as workflow steps):

- [ ] Lint check
- [ ] Type check
- [ ] Unit tests
- [ ] Integration tests
- [ ] E2E tests
- [ ] Security scan (e.g. `npm audit`)
- [ ] Bundle size check (if applicable)
- [ ] Code coverage threshold

## Comment Standards

- **Constructive:** Provide actionable feedback, not criticism
- **Specific:** Point to lines/files; explain the issue
- **Explain why:** Give reasoning for suggestions
- **Suggest alternatives:** Offer better approaches when possible
- **Acknowledge good work:** Recognise well-implemented features
